Enrollment for Preschool thru 12th grade will be August 5th from 7 am to 7 pm in the West Elementary Gym. Entry will be only at west elementary doors.
Enrollment packets will be sent in the mail by July 29th if you don’t have the packets by August 3rd please let us know.
We are asking that all the paperwork be filled out before you come to enrollment.
One person per family and masks are required. If you don’t have a mask one will be provided and temperature checks will be done.
We are requesting no students attend enrollment and there will be no schedule changes completed at this time. If you need to make changes to your schedule you will need to make an appointment with Mrs. Goeckel.
Social distancing is requested and attached is a map to show how enrollment will be set up.

post_text: Our USD 108 Reopening Schools committee has been working hard to provide guidelines to our own reopening schools. We had planned to start school on August 19, 2020 as our calendar indicated. Today, Governor Kelly, announced she will be issuing an Executive Order on Monday, July 20th that will delay the start of school until Wednesday, September 9 This means USD 108's first day with students will be on Wednesday, September 9th. Our administration and our committee were unaware of the plan to delay school until the news conference this afternoon. We will continue to move forward with making plans and preparing for our students to return to school.

Today, Governor Kelly, announced she will be issuing an Executive Order on Monday, July 20th that will delay the start of school until Wednesday, September 9 This means USD 108's first day with students will be on Wednesday, September 9th. Our administration and our committee were unaware of the plan to delay school until the news conference this afternoon. We will continue to move forward with making plans and preparing for our students to return to school.

post_text:
Tiger Pride Through and Through
American Pride – The Red, White and Blue

Your USD 108 Tigers are extending the opportunity to display our American spirit and pride. Our goal is to have every American in Washington County displaying our American flag outside. In doing so we are coming together to stand firm, tall and united against a small, but harmful creature that is attacking our very way of life. For those who do not have an American flag, we are gladly sharing all the small 24” flags that we use for our Veterans Day assemblies. We have more than enough of those to make sure every single household has a flag to post. The flags went out today (Monday) on the lunch deliveries. If you know of others who could use one, please contact Ms. Enyart at venyart@usd108.org

Together, the Red, White and Blue will succeed!

UPDATED INFORMATION ON MEAL PICK –UP
March 30, 2020

USD 108 has submitted and received a waiver to allow parents and guardians to pick up meals for children during the COVID-19 public health emergency. This waiver is effective immediately and remains in effect until June 30, 2020, or until expiration of the federally declared public health emergency, whichever is earlier.

USD 108 does ask that if this is the FIRST time you have received a meal, that you DO bring your child(ren) with you. This will allow us to verify students and families for record keeping purposes.

Let us know if you have questions.

text:
UPDATED INFORMATION ON MEAL PICK –UP
March 30, 2020

USD 108 has submitted and received a waiver to allow parents and guardians to pick up meals for children during the COVID-19 public health emergency. This waiver is effective immediately and remains in effect until June 30, 2020, or until expiration of the federally declared public health emergency, whichever is earlier.

USD 108 does ask that if this is the FIRST time you have received a meal, that you DO bring your child(ren) with you. This will allow us to verify students and families for record keeping purposes.

Let us know if you have questions.
lunch@usd108.org 785-325-2261x3

post_text: The recent events have changed all of our plans. My K-6 students had been learning about Reducing, Reusing, and .Recycling. We had planned on having a “Trashion Show” and modeling styles made from trash. The students were getting excited about doing this. We will do it next year, but it doesn’t mean you can’t have a “Trashion Show” at home! Collect items that would be thrown out and then design your own fashions made with paper, chip bags, whatever you can find. Get creative and please post your photos on Facebook! I would love to see how my kiddos are being creative! And don’t forget to Reduce, Reuse, and Recycle!

Whew…I don’t know if I knew the answer either, but luckily some of my high school students came through.

We have 3 winners: Abi Sawin, Michaela Jueneman, and Family Finlayson with the correct answer of “21”. Leave it up to Ms Jueneman, killing it as always, she showed her work!

We will be able to do this! Thanks to everyone who played…..WCHS rocks!
~Mrs. Hobbs

Bear =5, Flag = 4, Pot of Gold = 9, Hat = 3
9+3+9=21
13=5+3+5
5+4=5+4
9+4=4+9
21=9+5+4+3

Hello to all my 4th grade parents. This is a message from Mrs. Baker.

I was all geared up to see the kiddos this week. We were going to start adding and subtracting fractions, read new stories, learn more states and capitals, and finish researching and writing our Fish papers for the contest in art. Oh well, I guess we will wait a week.
I do not have any “work “ to give students this week, but I suggest spending some time on IReady math. Many students are getting closer and/or surpassing grade level topics on their IReady pathways. This is what we want and this is something they can do this week. I encourage them to read and do IReady this week!
Stay safe and healthy !

On the strong recommendation of the Kansas Department of Education, the Kansas Department of Health and Environment, and the Governors office, schools in Kansas will be closed the entire week of March 16 to 20. There is to be no student activities or spring practices. The buildings will be closed to all outside activities. The fitness room will also be closed.
USD 108 is working on a plan to provide a daily sack lunch with delivery in our surrounding communities, but this will take us a couple of days to organize, so please be patient. We will let you know when sack lunches are available.
Please stay tuned for additional information.
Thank you for understanding this unusual and unprecedented situation.
Supt Denise O'Dea

post_text: Mrs. Rundle’s second grade small group activity today was a STEM activity. The students had to work together to make a wind powered maze. Through this activity, they learned about the words: push, kinetic energy, friction, and obstacle. The students could only use connecting blocks to make it, they had to work together as a team to make a plan, And then build the maze and make any corrections to the plan that they discovered while making it. Then they raced the glitter balls through the maze using fat straws. Tomorrow, they will race again using different straws and balls to see what works the best to go through the maze the fastest. They learn teamwork, social end emotional skills, vocabulary and worked with numbers for this project.
